Prince Harry's ambushes on the Royal Family had a detrimental effect on the late Queen's health in her final year, it has been claimed. The Duke of Sussex's attacks are said to have “had an impact” on Elizabeth II's condition before she died last September. The late monarch had to cope with bombshell claims about the Firm, including those made in Harry and Meghan Markle's Oprah Winfrey interview, while the couple's Netflix show and the Duke's tell-all memoir loomed. A source close to the late Queen told the Telegraph: “This did have an impact on the Queen’s health in her final year. It did take its toll." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES ON THE ROYAL FAMILY: